    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Riggers called all stop to Crane Operator",
      "Tag lines pulled to lift assembly off rigger",
      "Injured person assisted to platform Medic",
      "Medical evacuation initiated via Search and Rescue helicopter",
      "Incident Command System response activated",
      "Injured person admitted to University Medical Center in New Orleans"
    ],
    "summary": "On March 21, 2023, at 16:45 hours, a rigger was caught between a wireline riser and gate valve assembly and a cargo basket during a blind lift crane operation on the H&P 204 platform at MC 854. The rigger sustained a nondisplaced L4 fracture, traumatic hernia, and pelvic muscle tear. The incident resulted from failure to identify and control pinch point hazards, inadequate barricading of the landing area, and crew members not following stop work authority and safe practice guidelines.",
